sentences: Love’s River was recognized as one of the best commercial productions by Will Ackerman after 2009.
San Francisco State University (CSU) and Academy of Art University have hosted her as a guest presenter in their music courses.

Sullivan composed the original soundtrack for the film Valentines Day Special, which starred Jon Polito, and performed the music for the track "Sleepwalking on a Tightrope" in the movie Wake, written by Henry LeRoy Finch.
She has also composed original music for Gunther Thallinger's short film Nine and A Half Minutes Left.
Sullivan performed on D. Edward’s album Love Is released in 2014.
In 2013, Sullivan performed on the album Sounds from the Circle V produced by Suzanne Doucet.
In 2014, Sullivan performed on the album Angel Blessings (Benefitting Hospice) produced by Lucinda Paulos.
Later in 2014, producer Will Ackerman and Tom Eaton featured her on their album The Gathering II.
